[13:47] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'this main page in the description below. Also this week this AI is pretty useful. It\'s called Causal Scene, and this is a video generation system that can create long interactive multi-shot videos in'

[13:59] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'real time. Here\'s how it works. So here\'s the interface and here\'s a demo of it in action. This Causal Scene is designed to stream video in real time following shot-level prompts from the'

[14:11] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'user. Now if you generate videos with multiple shots, they also need to be consistent, right? So this system also reuses memory from earlier shots, so the story and the scene remains consistent'

[14:23] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'throughout the entire video. So this is almost like a director giving instructions. It\'s taking in a sequence of prompts and then it streams a multi-shot video. The key idea is this causal generation, which means it'

[14:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'generates forward in time without needing to recompute everything from the beginning. So you can append a new direction while it\'s already generating with your prompt, and the system just keeps going. Now if you compare this new'

[14:48] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Causal Scene with other long video generators like Infinity Rope, Long Live, Mem Flow, and Self-Forcing, which I\'ve gone over on my channel before, notice that this new one is a lot more consistent. The character actually looks'

[15:01] [scene:talk]
