AUDIO: 'GDO-1 moves way more smoothly. Also this week, we have an incredibly useful 3D model generator called Articraft. This can generate articulated 3D objects. In other words, objects that actually move.'

[29:06] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'So these are 3D assets that are made of parts, joints, hinges, sliders, wheels, and other moving mechanisms. This takes a simple object description, such as the prompt over here, and outputs a working'

[29:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '3D asset with separate parts and realistic motion. Here\'s an example of a desk lamp with a rectangular base. Or here is a three-link chain for compact mechanical linkage. Here\'s an even more'

[29:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'impressive example of a mechanical keyboard. Or here\'s a jet engine. The clever part is that Articraft turns the 3D asset generation into a coding problem. Instead of asking the AI to directly imagine a final 3D mesh in one'

[29:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'shot, it asks an AI coding agent like GPT-5.5 to write a program that builds the object. That program defines the geometry, the parts, the joints, and'

[29:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'tests that check whether the object makes sense. So the AI is coding up all these separate parts and also checking to make sure that the parts are actually linked correctly together. And this'

[30:07] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'matters because articulated objects are everywhere in the real world. So if you\'re designing 3D assets, you also need to know how multiple parts move and work together. And Articraft is trying to automate this entire pipeline. And'

[30:19] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the scale is the really impressive part. The team built a dataset called Articraft-10K, which contains more than 10,000 articulated 3D assets across 245 categories. This includes everyday'

[30:32] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'objects, mechanical stuff, furniture, appliances, tools, and other stuff. So this would be super useful for robotic simulation, like teaching robotic arms how to manipulate certain objects. Or'

[30:44] [scene:talk]
