[33:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'pro users in the US on web and iOS. If you\'re interested in reading further, I\'ll link to this main page in the description below. Also this week, we have a new AI called Track Crafter. This'

[33:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'can take a video and try to follow every pixel through 3D space. So, here\'s a tricky breakdancing video. It tries to map out each pixel of the dancer as they move. Or, here\'s another example where'

[33:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'it tries to map the flow of the pixels of the dogs as they move around. Now, this could be very useful for understanding dynamic scenes or segmenting things or detecting movement, for example, in surveillance. The clever'

[33:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'part is that Track Crafter repurposes a video diffusion model. Now, video models are, of course, trained to generate videos. They learn motion patterns from huge amounts of internet data. Well, Track Crafter takes these motion'

[33:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'instincts and redirects them towards motion tracking. So, instead of just generating what each frame should look like, it learns to follow reference points across time. So, this allows the system to predict these 3D trajectories of various pixels in the video. And in'

[34:09] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'terms of pixel tracking, it even beats other competitors like Motion Tracker and Any 4D, which I\'ve gone over before. So, you can see on average, Track Crafter scores the highest out of these benchmarks. It\'s also much better at'

[34:22] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'handling long videos and large motion. And this is also way more efficient. This can generate things faster and it takes up less memory. The awesome thing is they\'ve released this already. So, if'

